OCCURRENCE. — ffle stratigraphical range of this species is from the Upper Paleocene ( Pajaud & Plaziat 1972 ) to Recent. Its Recent representatives are living in the south-western part of the Mediterranean Sea at the depth of 1-110 m ( Logan 2007 ) and are regarded as a neoendemic species (
Logan et al . 2004
). It is in fact a relict distribution because in the Eocene it is recorded throughout Europe but in the Neogene it is known only from the Mediterranean region.
